CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 5, 1965, pg. 6, reads: "The Twilighters Club - celebrated its 20th anniversary this year by entertaining their mothers, mothers-in-law, aunts and other relatives at a dinner recently. Held at Weinstein's Kennilworth Restaurant, Mrs. Eric Springer was guest speaker.  Left to right, seated: Mrs. Carolyn Kirkland, Mrs. Theodore Ford, president, and Mrs. Charlotte Grimes.  Standing: Mmes. Bobetta Johnson, Norma Grant, Ann Harris, Claudia Davis, Eleanor Burden, Vivian Colbert and Hattie Smith.  Missing from the picture are Mmes. Thelma Thompson, Kathryn Woodruff and Gloria Smith. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women in the Twilighters Club, including Mrs. Theodore Ford, Hattie Smith, unknown, Norma Grant, and Charlotte Grimes second from right, standing behind banquet tables, in Weinstein's Restaurant, in Kennilworth Building, East Liberty
